race.comment: CANTILEVER (1) shed the maiden tag last start over the 1400m journey at this track after knocking on the door for a little while. That may be the kickstart he needs to go on with the job now. Likely to get back from the draw but was well fancied under similar circumstances two back and can repeat the dose. BE MY BELLE (3) sat on the speed last time out and was just too strong over this track and trip, scoring by 0.6L. Yuill remains in the saddle and she maps for a similar run today from a good draw. Unbeaten at this track and trip and can be hard to beat once again. ROCK DEE JAY (10) turned in an improved effort last start at Ascot when on the quick turnaround. He'll find this a little easier coming back to country level and he maps to get every chance from the draw. Can put his best foot forward. YALLINGUP GIRL (6) is better than she showed last time out and can bounce back. BEST RESULT (4) can be in the finish.
